@startuml

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
}
skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    DiamondBorderColor #6C757D
}
skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleBackgroundColor #DEE2E6
    TitleFontColor #212529
    TitleFontSize 12
}

title OpenTracer Scope Management\n<size:11><color:#6C757D>OpenTracer1 / OpenTracer adapters: activating spans, retrieving active scope, unwrapping to DDTrace native scope</color></size>

|Caller|
start

fork
  ' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  ' FLOW 1 — activate()
  ' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  :invoke **ScopeManager::activate**(OTSpan $span, $finishSpanOnClose);
  note right
    OT1 adapter: strict **bool** type hint (PHP 7.1+)
    OT  adapter: untyped param (PHP 5/7 compatible)
    Both adapters are **final** classes
  end note

  |OpenTracer Adapter\n(OT1 / OT ScopeManager)|

  if (Is $span an instance of\nadapter **Span** class?) then (yes)
    :Call **$span->unwrapped()**\nto obtain native DDTrace\\Span;
  else (no)
    :Call **Span::toDDSpan($span)**\nto convert foreign OTSpan\nto native DDTrace\\Span;
  endif

  :Call **$this->scopeManager->activate**(nativeSpan, $finishSpanOnClose)\non underlying DDTrace\\ScopeManager;

  |DDTrace ScopeManager\n(Native)|

  :Create new **DDTrace\\Scope**\n($this, $nativeSpan, $finishSpanOnClose);

  if (Is $span a DDTrace\\Span AND\n**ObjectKVStore** key\n'ddtrace_scope_activated' present?) then (yes)
    :ObjectKVStore::put($span->internalSpan,\n'ddtrace_scope_activated', true);
    note right
      Cross-layer sync flag —\ntracks spans activated\nfrom userland
    end note
  else (no / skip)
  endif

  :Push new **DDTrace\\Scope** onto **$scopes[]** stack\n<size:10>(LIFO order)</size>;

  if (Does $span->getContext()->**isHostRoot()**?) then (yes)
    :Also push scope to **$hostRootScopes[]**;
    note right
      Tracks distributed-tracing\nroot spans — all host root\nscopes closed on ScopeManager::close()
    end note
  else (no)
  endif

  :Return **DDTrace\\Scope** instance;

  |OpenTracer Adapter\n(OT1 / OT ScopeManager)|

  :Wrap DDTrace\\Scope in new\n**OpenTracer1\\Scope** / **OpenTracer\\Scope**\n(OT wrapper);

  |Caller|

  :Receive **OTScope wrapper**;

fork again
  ' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  ' FLOW 2 — getActive()
  ' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  :invoke **ScopeManager::getActive()**;

  |OpenTracer Adapter\n(OT1 / OT ScopeManager)|

  :Forward to **$this->scopeManager->getActive()**\non underlying DDTrace\\ScopeManager;

  |DDTrace ScopeManager\n(Native)|

  :Call **reconcileInternalAndUserland()**;

  note right
    Reconciles PHP userland scope stack\nwith C-extension internal span stack\non every getActive() call
  end note

  :Walk **$scopes[]** from top downward;

  repeat
    if (Scope's span is **finished**?) then (yes)
      :Remove scope from **$scopes[]**\n<size:10>(sync userland with C-extension engine)</size>;
    else (no — span still active)
      :Set as **$topScope**;
      break
    endif
  repeat while (More scopes in stack?) is (yes)

  if (**$scopes[]** is now empty?) then (yes)
    |DDTrace C-Extension\n(root_span / active_span)|

    :Call **root_span()**\n<size:10>(DDTrace C-extension global function)</size>;

    if (Root span exists?) then (yes)
      :Build new **DDTrace\\Scope**\nwrapping root span;
      :Push to **$scopes[0]**;
    else (no)
      |DDTrace ScopeManager\n(Native)|
      :Return **null**;
    endif

    |DDTrace C-Extension\n(root_span / active_span)|

    :Call **active_span()**\n<size:10>(DDTrace C-extension global function)</size>\nto discover internally-activated spans;

    |DDTrace ScopeManager\n(Native)|

    :FOR each internal span\n**not yet in userland scopes**:\ncreate new DDTrace\\Scope, prepend to stack;
  else (scopes remain)
  endif

  :Walk reconciled **$scopes[]** from top downward;

  repeat
    if ($span is NOT DDTrace\\Span\nOR ObjectKVStore\n'ddtrace_scope_activated' is truthy?) then (yes)
      :Return this **DDTrace\\Scope** as active;
      break
    endif
  repeat while (More scopes?) is (yes)

  |OpenTracer Adapter\n(OT1 / OT ScopeManager)|

  if (Returned DDTrace\\Scope is **null**?) then (yes)
    |Caller|
    :Return **null** to caller;
  else (no — scope found)
    :Wrap DDTrace\\Scope in new\n**OpenTracer1\\Scope** / **OpenTracer\\Scope**\n(OT wrapper);

    |Caller|
    :Receive **OTScope wrapper**;
  endif

fork again
  ' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  ' FLOW 3 — unwrapped()
  ' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  :invoke **ScopeManager::unwrapped()**;

  |OpenTracer Adapter\n(OT1 / OT ScopeManager)|

  :Return **$this->scopeManager**\n(the DDTrace\\Contracts\\ScopeManager instance);

  note right
    Bypasses the OT adapter entirely —\ncaller receives the native\nDDTrace ScopeManager directly
  end note

  |Caller|

  :Hold native **DDTrace\\ScopeManager**\nand call DDTrace-specific APIs directly;

end fork

stop

@enduml
